{"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.DiophantineApproximation","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.Computation.ApproximationCorollaries","Mathlib.Algebra.ContinuedFractions.Computation.Translations","Mathlib.Combinatorics.Pigeonhole","Mathlib.Data.Int.Units","Mathlib.Data.Real.Irrational","Mathlib.RingTheory.Coprime.Lemmas","Mathlib.Tactic.Basic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L606-L610","name":"Real.exists_continued_fraction_convergent_eq_rat","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_continued_fraction_convergent_eq_rat","doc":"The main result, *Legendre's Theorem* on rational approximation:\nif `ξ` is a real number and  `q` is a rational number such that `|ξ - q| < 1/(2*q.den^2)`,\nthen `q` is a convergent of the continued fraction expansion of `ξ`.\nThis is the version using `generalized_contined_fraction.convergents`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L588-L599","name":"Real.exists_rat_eq_convergent","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_rat_eq_convergent","doc":"The main result, *Legendre's Theorem* on rational approximation:\nif `ξ` is a real number and  `q` is a rational number such that `|ξ - q| < 1/(2*q.den^2)`,\nthen `q` is a convergent of the continued fraction expansion of `ξ`.\nThis version uses `Real.convergent`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L538-L581","name":"Real.exists_rat_eq_convergent'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_rat_eq_convergent'","doc":"The technical version of *Legendre's Theorem*. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L408-L410","name":"Real.ContfracLegendre.Ass","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.ContfracLegendre.Ass","doc":"Define the technical condition to be used as assumption in the inductive proof. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L384-L390","name":"Real.continued_fraction_convergent_eq_convergent","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.continued_fraction_convergent_eq_convergent","doc":"The `n`th convergent of the `GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of ξ`\nagrees with `ξ.convergent n`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L368-L372","name":"Real.convergent_of_int","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.convergent_of_int","doc":"If `ξ` is an integer, all its convergents equal `ξ`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L360-L363","name":"Real.convergent_of_zero","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.convergent_of_zero","doc":"All convergents of `0` are zero. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L351-L355","name":"Real.convergent_succ","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.convergent_succ","doc":"The `(n+1)`th convergent of `ξ` is the `n`th convergent of `1/(fract ξ)`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L345-L346","name":"Real.convergent_zero","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.convergent_zero","doc":"The zeroth convergent of `ξ` is `⌊ξ⌋`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L338-L340","name":"Real.convergent","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.convergent","doc":"We give a direct recursive definition of the convergents of the continued fraction\nexpansion of a real number `ξ`. The main reason for that is that we want to have the\nconvergents as rational numbers; the versions\n`(GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of ξ).convergents` and\n`(GeneralizedContinuedFraction.of ξ).convergents'` always give something of the\nsame type as `ξ`. We can then also use dot notation `ξ.convergent n`.\nAnother minor reason is that this demonstrates that the proof\nof Legendre's theorem does not need anything beyond this definition.\nWe provide a proof that this definition agrees with the other one;\nsee `Real.continued_fraction_convergent_eq_convergent`.\n(Note that we use the fact that `1/0 = 0` here to make it work for rational `ξ`.) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L291-L298","name":"Real.infinite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq_iff_irrational","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.infinite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq_iff_irrational","doc":"The set of good rational approximations to a real number `ξ` is infinite if and only if\n`ξ` is irrational. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L266-L284","name":"Rat.finite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Rat.finite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq","doc":"A rational number has only finitely many good rational approximations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L236-L262","name":"Rat.den_le_and_le_num_le_of_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Rat.den_le_and_le_num_le_of_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq","doc":"If `ξ` is rational, then the good rational approximations to `ξ` have bounded\nnumerator and denominator. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L208-L215","name":"Real.infinite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq_of_irrational","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.infinite_rat_abs_sub_lt_one_div_den_sq_of_irrational","doc":"If `ξ` is an irrational real number, then there are infinitely many good\nrational approximations to `ξ`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L186-L203","name":"Real.exists_rat_abs_sub_lt_and_lt_of_irrational","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_rat_abs_sub_lt_and_lt_of_irrational","doc":"Given any rational approximation `q` to the irrational real number `ξ`, there is\na good rational approximation `q'` such that `|ξ - q'| < |ξ - q|`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L156-L167","name":"Real.exists_rat_abs_sub_le_and_den_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_rat_abs_sub_le_and_den_le","doc":"*Dirichlet's approximation theorem:*\nFor any real number `ξ` and positive natural `n`, there is a fraction `q`\nsuch that `q.den ≤ n` and `|ξ - q| ≤ 1/((n+1)*q.den)`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L145-L150","name":"Real.exists_nat_abs_mul_sub_round_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_nat_abs_mul_sub_round_le","doc":"*Dirichlet's approximation theorem:*\nFor any real number `ξ` and positive natural `n`, there is a natural number `k`,\nwith `0 < k ≤ n` such that `|k*ξ - round(k*ξ)| ≤ 1/(n+1)`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.lean#L98-L138","name":"Real.exists_int_int_abs_mul_sub_le","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/DiophantineApproximation.html#Real.exists_int_int_abs_mul_sub_le","doc":"*Dirichlet's approximation theorem:*\nFor any real number `ξ` and positive natural `n`, there are integers `j` and `k`,\nwith `0 < k ≤ n` and `|k*ξ - j| ≤ 1/(n+1)`.\n\nSee also `Real.exists_nat_abs_mul_sub_round_le`. "}]}